judges: HON'BLE MR. JUSTICE RAJAN GUPTA Present
judgment_text:
IN THE HIGH COURT OF PUNJAB AND HARYANA AT CHANDIGARH
Civil Writ Petition No.15035 of 1989 
DATE OF DECISION: March 16, 2010
M/s. Kansal Rice Mills and others
.....Petitioners
versus
The State of Punjab and others
 .....Respondents
CORAM:- 
HON'BLE MR. JUSTICE RAJAN GUPTA
Present: Mr.Mansur Ali, Advocate for the petitioners
Ms.Sudeepti Sharma, Deputy Advocate General, 
Punjab 
Mr.S.S. Brar, Advocate for respondent No.5
..
RAJAN GUPTA, J.: (Oral)
Learned State counsel submits that the Punjab
Rice Brand (Levy) Control Order, 1988, is no longer in
existence. According to her, this petition has, thus, been
rendered infructuous. Learned counsel for the petitioners
does not dispute this factual position.
In view of the above, the writ petition is
dismissed as having been rendered infructuous.
March 16, 2010

 ( RAJAN GUPTA )
pc
 JUDGE
